		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Ant colony optimization</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:202px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Safari_ants.jpg" class="image" title="Ant behavior was the inspiration for the metaheuristic optimization technique"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/34/Safari_ants.jpg/200px-Safari_ants.jpg" width="200" height="133" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Safari_ants.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
Ant behavior was the inspiration for the metaheuristic optimization technique</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>The <b>ant colony optimization</b> <a href="/wiki/Algorithm" title="Algorithm">algorithm</a> (ACO), is a <a href="/wiki/Probability" title="Probability">probabilistic</a> technique for solving computational problems which can be reduced to finding good paths through <a href="/wiki/Graph_(mathematics)" title="Graph (mathematics)">graphs</a>.</p>
<p>This algorithm is a member of <b>ant colony algorithms</b> family, in <a href="/wiki/Swarm_intelligence" title="Swarm intelligence">swarm intelligence</a> methods, and it constitutes some <a href="/wiki/Metaheuristic" title="Metaheuristic">metaheuristic</a> optimizations. Initially proposed by <a href="/wiki/Marco_Dorigo" title="Marco Dorigo">Marco Dorigo</a> in 1992 in his PhD thesis <sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> <sup id="cite_ref-M._Dorigo.2C_Optimization.2C_Learning_and_Natural_Algorithms_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-M._Dorigo.2C_Optimization.2C_Learning_and_Natural_Algorithms-1" title=""><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup> , the first algorithm was aiming to search for an optimal path in a graph; based on the behavior of <a href="/wiki/Ants" title="Ants" class="mw-redirect">ants</a> seeking a path between their <a href="/wiki/Ant_colony" title="Ant colony">colony</a> and a source of food. The original idea has since diversified to solve a wider class of Numerical problems, and as a result, several problems have emerged, drawing on various aspects of the behavior of ants.</p>
